cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is about face completion using a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) under structured occlusions. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to disentangling and fusing clean faces and occlusions, which involves learning transformations from unpaired data. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on Meshface verification, which involves 3D modeling and graphics, suggesting that it may also belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-categories.
